If the bus takes 40 minutes to complete 80 miles of a trip, Amanda's car, which takes 5 fewer minutes to complete a trip than the bus, will take 40-5=<<40-5=53>>53 minutes to complete the trip.
A round trip will take the car twice the time for going one way, a total of 53+53=<<53+53=106>>106
